            <who name="Thomas Herchenroeder">thron7</who>
            <bug_when>2009-02-27 11:39:00 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The default &#39;lint&#39; job should honor config include/exclude settings, so you can 
narrow down the classes within a library that you want to be lint-checked.

This will allow to run lint on arbitrary filtered class lists. The default 
settings for the job will make sure lint is only applied to the local library 
classes, but this can be overridden by custom job settings in the config.

The same basically applies to the &#39;fix&#39; and &#39;pretty&#39; jobs. It might make sense 
to taylor those along the same principles.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
